Senior Client Advisors




Jayson S. DeAngelis, CFP®						        						                Partner, Senior Client Advisor, & Director of Business Development




Jayson is a Partner, Senior Client Advisor, and the Director of Business Development at the firm.

In his role, Jayson leads several of the firm’s largest client engagements and is also responsible for coordinating the business development efforts across the firm. In his work directly with client families, Jayson draws on his experience growing up and working in his own family’s business to help navigate the often complex relationship between family dynamics and the management of wealth.

Prior to joining the firm in 2006, Jayson worked as a Wealth Management Advisor in Merrill Lynch’s Global Private Client group where he built a practice serving over thirty families and focused primarily on the financial planning issues faced by small business owners.

Jayson graduated from George Washington University with a BBA in finance.  He is a CERTIFIED FINANCIAL PLANNER™ practitioner. Jayson is a member of the CFA Institute and the Boston Security Analyst’s Society.

Jayson is a competitive triathlete and an avid skier.  Jayson and his wife, Elena, live in North Reading, MA with their three daughters.  




Jennifer M. Eaton, JD						        						                Partner & Senior Client Advisor




Jennifer M. Eaton is a Partner and Senior Client Advisor at the firm. Jennifer, along with Christopher C. Chandler, CFA, CAIA, leads the Florida office for the firm. In her work with families, Jennifer draws on her extensive legal knowledge and expertise and wealth planning skills to assist families to define, articulate and achieve their various planning goals. She also enjoys working directly with families on non-estate and tax planning matters and spends significant time working with next generation family members to better prepare them to be good stewards of their family’s wealth.

Prior to joining the firm, Jennifer was a Vice President and Senior Family Wealth Advisor with GenSpring Family Offices for more than nine-years where she worked with wealthy families on a range of subjects including the oversight of tax and estate planning issues, philanthropic endeavors, family governance matters, trusteeship, and coordination of the flow of information with outside professionals.

Jennifer is an active member of the Florida Bar and was an estate and tax planning practitioner and Partner at a boutique law firm in Coral Gables, FL until 2006.  In her legal practice, Jennifer worked with high net worth families to identify and solve for her clients’ unique and often complex estate planning and asset transfer goals and objectives.

Jennifer earned her Juris Doctor from the University of Miami School of Law and attended the University of South Carolina where she received a B.S. in Criminal Justice. Jennifer is a founding member of Impact The Palm Beaches and an active member of the Palm Beach and Martin County Estate Planning Councils. Additionally, she is a member of the Elder Law, Real Property, and Probate and Trust Law sections of the Florida Bar.  




Stephen H. Hopkins, CPA						        						                Shareholder & Senior Client Advisor




Stephen is a Shareholder & Senior Client Advisor at the firm. Prior to joining the firm in 2016, Stephen was the Vice Chairman at Roundtable Investment Partners where he was responsible for delivering strategic advice and planning, investment management, and merchant banking services to some of the firm’s largest and most complex relationships.  Previously, Stephen was Co-Head, President and Chief Operating Officer of Citigroup Asset Management, a global money management firm with over $400 billion in assets under management and served as head of Citigroup’s Private Bank Asset Management Group and led Global Product Management for The Citigroup Private Bank.  In 2005, he led the sale of the Asset Management Division to Legg Mason, Inc. He subsequently joined Legg Mason, Inc. as a Senior Vice President with responsibility for a number of senior level initiatives related to the integration of CAM. Mr. Hopkins was formerly Chief Operating Officer for Asset Management Services at JPMorgan and later joined the Private Bank to launch Morgan’s largest internet venture, Morgan OnLine, the first private bank on the web. He was instrumental in the formation and development of Goldman Sachs Asset Management as a diversified global money management firm where he served as its Chief Financial Officer. Previously he was a Senior Manager in the Capital Markets Practice, at Arthur Andersen & Co.

Stephen served on the Executive Committee and Board of Governors of the Investment Company Institute for over a decade. At Citigroup, he served on the board of CitiStreet, a joint venture of Citigroup and State Street bank, which was the 2nd largest 401(k) administrator in the United States. Stephen is currently on the board of Fund Evaluation Group, an institutional investment consulting, portfolio management and research firm and SRL Global, a financial services technology company. He has extensive leadership and hands-on operating experience.

Stephen graduated from the University of Rhode Island and is a Certified Public Accountant (CPA).

Stephen has a home in Gilmanton, New Hampshire.  He is a skilled chef and an expert on fine wines and his wife, Judy, is a very serious gardener.  




Sheila C. Lawrence, MALD, CFP®						        						                Managing Director & Senior Client Advisor




Sheila is a Managing Director and Senior Client Advisor at the firm.  A significant portion of Sheila's practice involves estate planning, wealth transfer and investment management with a particular focus on financial education and coaching for the rising generation.  Sheila works closely with each member of a family to ensure continuation of money values from one generation to the next.

Prior to joining the firm in 2007, Sheila earned a Master of Arts in Law and Diplomacy (MALD) from The Fletcher School of Law and Diplomacy, concentrating on international business and international trade policy.  She completed an internship in Singapore with the Government of Singapore Investment Corporation, researching emerging market investment risk management.  Prior to that, Sheila worked at Bear Stearns & Co., Inc. in the credit risk management department.  She managed credit risks across the firm's derivatives transactions portfolio, including those for high net worth clients.

Sheila graduated from the University of California at Berkeley, Summa Cum Laude, Phi Beta Kappa, with a B.A. in Economics. Sheila is a CERTIFIED FINANCIAL PLANNER™ practitioner and is a current co-chair of the Professional Advisors Network at The Boston Foundation.

Sheila has a life-long background and interest in dance, and is particularly passionate about environmental conservation and sustainable agriculture. She serves on the board of the Lexington Community Farm Coalition.  She and her husband, Jason, have two young children and live in Lexington, MA. Sheila speaks Mandarin Chinese.  




Stephen A. Martone, MSFP, CFP®						        						                Managing Director & Senior Client Advisor




Stephen is a Managing Director, Senior Client Advisor, and the Director of Wealth Advisory Operations at the firm. While responsible for multiple areas of wealth management, a significant portion of his practice is focused on wealth transfer techniques and estate plan structure. Stephen has expertise in cash flow planning and modeling, providing his clients with a holistic view that captures the interaction between investment management and personal spending.

As Director of Wealth Advisory Operations, his primary focus is on optimizing the organizational effectiveness of the wealth advisory practice. This is done through identifying process inefficiencies, thinking creatively to develop a solution, and engaging and motivating staff while providing the leadership throughout implementation. Stephen provides oversight of the wealth advisory staff with supervision and hiring responsibility of the Wealth Planners and Planning Associates.

Stephen is a CERTIFIED FINANCIAL PLANNER™ practitioner. Prior to joining the firm in 2005, Stephen received a Master of Science in Financial Planning (MSFP), with distinction, from McCallum Graduate School of Business at Bentley University and a BS in Finance, Magna Cum Laude, from Bentley University. While at Bentley, he was a member of Beta Gamma Sigma International Honor Society, and was actively involved in community outreach programs.

Stephen resides in the Boston area and during his free time enjoys attending Celtics games with his wife and coaching in a youth basketball league.  




Adam Ochlis, CPA, MST						        						                Partner & Senior Client Advisor




Adam is a Partner and Senior Client Advisor at the firm. While responsible for multiple areas of wealth management, he has a particular expertise in income tax planning for high net worth individuals. He keeps abreast of tax developments and informs the firm of changes in legislation and implications for the firm's clients.

Before joining the firm in 2007, Adam was a tax supervisor at Levine, Katz, Nannis & Solomon, P.C., an accounting firm in Needham, MA, where he provided tax planning and compliance, financial statement preparation, and other accounting services to high net worth individuals and privately held companies. Prior to that, he worked at KPMG Consulting (now part of Deloitte), where he helped the United States Department of Defense improve and streamline various finance and accounting processes. Adam also spent nearly 10 years as an economist and policy analyst for the U.S. Departments of Labor and Education.

Adam received a Masters in Taxation from Bentley University, his Certificate in Accounting from the University of Virginia, and a Bachelor of Arts in Economics and Communications from the University of Michigan. He is a Certified Public Accountant (CPA).

Adam is on the Finance Committee of Jewish Family and Children's Service. During his free time, Adam enjoys playing golf and tennis, following New England sports, and planning his family's next vacation. He lives with his wife, Eve, and their two teenagers in Newton, MA.  




Jeff Potter						        						                Managing Director & Senior Client Advisor




Jeff is a Managing Director and Senior Client Advisor at the firm. Prior to joining in 2014, he opened his own consulting firm, Esker Capital, to focus on providing operating and consulting services to businesses in the family office sector. Prior to starting Esker Capital, Jeff was a Partner and Chief Operating Officer at Capital Resource Partners, a private equity firm focused on investing in lower middle market companies.

Prior to Capital Resource Partners, Jeff was Vice President of Corporate Development for Reeves Industries, Inc., a family owned manufacturing company with operations in the United States and Europe. Early in his career, Jeff worked for CS First Boston in their restructuring group advising debtors and creditors and for Chemical Bank as a commercial lending officer executing leveraged loan transactions.

Jeff has an MBA from Yale with a concentration in Finance and a BA from Williams College.

Jeff enjoys hockey, hiking, outdoor activities, art history and traveling. Jeff and his family live in Weston, MA.  




