Sarah E. Ludden						        						                Wealth Planning Associate




Sarah is a Wealth Planning Associate at the firm.

Before joining the firm, Sarah worked at Fiduciary Trust Company where she had been for 8 years, most recently as a Senior Account Administrator, working with two financial advisors on 350 accounts, processing and monitoring the accuracy of asset transactions, creating customized financial reports, and fostering relationships with client families, foundations, and professionals.  Prior to that, she worked for State Street Financial as a Mutual Fund Account Controller and Ameriprise as a Financial Advisor.

Sarah graduated from Northeastern University with a Bachelor’s in Business Administration. She is currently pursuing her CFP® designation through Boston University’s Center for Professional Education.  Sarah is the Chair of the Forte539 Advisory Council for the Boston Center for the Arts and is a member of the Leadership Circle and Steering Committee for the Project Bread Walk for Hunger. She is also a member of the Financial Planners Association of Massachusetts.

Sarah and her husband live in the Greater Boston area, with their Yellow Lab, Honey.  She enjoys an active lifestyle through hiking, yoga and running and also enjoys writing poetry and traveling.  




Erik A. Palmason						        						                Wealth Planning Associate




Erik is a Wealth Planning Associate at the firm.

Prior to joining Ballentine Partners, Erik worked for the Bank of New York Mellon as a Global Income and Tax Specialist. In Erik’s Asset Servicing role, he processed dividend and interest income and filed tax reclaims for large institutional investors. His efforts focused on Swiss and Danish equities and debt securities.

Erik earned a Bachelor of Arts degree in Political Science from Allegheny College where he was active in service and community outreach. Erik served as Philanthropy Chairman in Phi Kappa Psi. His chapter was formally recognized for Philanthropic achievement, effectively bridging the gap between school and surrounding community by providing upwards of 2,000 hours of service per academic year.

Currently, Erik is pursuing his CERTIFIED FINANCIAL PLANNER™ practitioner designation through Boston University.

Erik is a Finance Committee member for the Congregational Church of Littleton, and spends his free time playing golf, traveling, and boating. He currently resides in Watertown, MA.  




Christian Stahlman, MSFP						        						                Wealth Planning Associate




Christian is a Wealth Planning Associate at the firm.

Prior to joining the firm in 2016, he was a Financial Planning Assistant at New England Private Wealth Advisors in Wellesley, MA where he assisted Senior Client Advisors in preparing client materials ranging from the updating of client’s financials to the preparing of tax summaries.  While in college, he was also an intern at Baystate Financial, Morgan Stanley, and Barclays Wealth in London.

Christian graduated Cum Laude from Bentley University with a Bachelor of Science in Corporate Finance and Accounting and graduated from the McCallum Graduate School of Business with a Master of Science in Financial Planning.  He also received a Certificate in Taxation during his time in the graduate program.

Currently, he is pursuing the CERTIFIED FINANCIAL PLANNER™ practitioner designation and planning to sit for the exam this year. He has been a member of the Financial Planning Association since 2015 and is also a member of NexGen, a community of FPA members focusing on the next generation of financial professionals. He lives in The Palm Beaches, and in his free time, Christian enjoys golfing, exercising, and playing classical piano.  




Morgan Williams						        						                Wealth Planning Associate




Morgan is a Wealth Planning Associate at the firm.

Prior to joining the firm in 2009, Morgan worked at Community Bank & Trust Co. in Wolfeboro NH, first as a teller, then loan servicer, and finally as a staff accountant until the bank was bought out by Chittenden Corporation and merged with Ocean Bank in 2008.

Morgan received a Bachelor of Arts Degree in Psychology from Regis College with a concentration in Business Management.

Morgan is a co-founder of Assistance Canine Training Services (A.C.T.S), a non-profit organization that raises and trains service dogs for people with mobility problems. Morgan volunteers as a puppy raiser/trainer for the organization.  







